Rating: 4
So, I love this recipe (it's been my go-to spontaneous dinner party recipe for almost a year), but I have to say, that I've never got it quite right. Either I forget to butter/flour the pan before I put down by pizza dough, or I forget the salt and pepper, or I overcook the potatoes...I don't think I've ever carried this recipe out flawlessly before. So word of warning: don't oversimplify this recipe in your mind! I tend to think of the few things I need (potatoes, dough, cream, thyme) and then throw it all together without much thought. Mistake. But still yummy.

Rating: 4
This is a GREAT recipe. I did make some changes though. I used rosemary instead of thyme (just because I had some) and added caramelized onions. The caramelized onions were my favorite part, so I definitely recommend adding those. The pizza was a little dry overall, so I might try adding the creme fraiche a few minutes into the cooking time when I make this again. This is one of my new favorite pizza recipes!

